					<description><![CDATA[<p>SpaceX Lands Major AI Infrastructure Contract SpaceX has secured a computing agreement worth up to $6.3 billion with open-source artificial intelligence startup Reflection AI. The deal grants Reflection access to</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/spacex-secures-6-3b-compute-deal-with-reflection-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal">SpaceX Secures $6.3B Compute Deal With Reflection AI</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>SpaceX Lands Major AI Infrastructure Contract</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">SpaceX has secured a computing agreement worth up to $6.3 billion with open-source artificial intelligence startup Reflection AI. The deal grants Reflection access to Nvidia GB300 chips housed at SpaceX’s Colossus 2 data centre in Memphis, Tennessee. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Under the agreement, Reflection will pay $150 million per month starting July 1, 2026. The contract could remain in place through 2029, although either company may terminate it with 90 days’ notice after the initial three-month period. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The agreement represents another significant milestone for SpaceX as it expands its AI infrastructure business beyond internal projects. Originally built for xAI and Grok, Colossus now serves external AI developers commercially.</span></p>
<h2><b>Reflection AI Expands Open-Source Ambitions</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Reflection AI joins companies using Colossus infrastructure for next-generation artificial intelligence development. Google, Anthropic, and Cursor are existing customers with over eighty billion dollars committed through 2029.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2024 by ex-DeepMind engineers Misha Laskin and Ioannis Antonoglou at Google. Reflection raised 130 million dollars initially, then secured 2 billion more in 2025 funding rounds. Investors include Nvidia, Sequoia Capital, and Lightspeed, supporting the startup’s rapid growth trajectory.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The startup develops open-source AI models intended for public sector and enterprise usage globally. </span><a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/model" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Models</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> are designed for use rather than closed proprietary systems controlled by single vendors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Customers prefer transparency, avoiding black-box systems and seeking full control over AI operations. They want system inspection, customization, and security tailored to their specific organizational requirements.</span></p>
<h2><b>Colossus Continues Rapid Growth</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203026" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203026" class="size-full wp-image-203026" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/SpaceX-2.png" alt="Illustration of the Colossus AI computing platform showing massive GPU infrastructure, hyperscale data centres, and interconnected AI companies sharing compute resources." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203026" class="wp-caption-text">The Colossus platform is rapidly scaling into one of the world’s largest AI computing environments, driven by soaring demand for GPU capacity and expanding infrastructure partnerships across the global AI ecosystem. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">SpaceX’s Colossus platform has become one of the largest AI computing environments in operation. The facility reportedly contains around 555,000 Nvidia GPUs acquired through investments estimated at $18 billion. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Expansion plans could eventually increase power capacity to as much as two gigawatts. Commercial demand for the infrastructure has grown rapidly. Anthropic committed $45 billion, while Google signed a $30 billion Colossus infrastructure agreement.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Access to advanced AI chips remains a major challenge across the industry. By leasing capacity from SpaceX, Reflection avoids the enormous cost of building and operating data centres. The arrangement also provides immediate access to cutting-edge hardware.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Reflection’s contract adds another major customer and revenue stream. The agreement also highlights the interconnected nature of the AI industry, where companies frequently serve as suppliers, customers, and investors within the same ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/cadence-raises-100m-expand-ai-chronic-care/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Cadence Raises $100M to Expand AI-Powered Chronic Care Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><b>AI Infrastructure Spending Reaches New Highs</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Reflection deal comes as spending on AI infrastructure continues to accelerate worldwide. Technology companies are investing heavily in data centres, chips, networking equipment, and cloud platforms to support increasingly complex AI workloads.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For SpaceX, the agreement further diversifies revenue sources beyond its traditional aerospace operations. The company’s growing presence in AI infrastructure positions it to benefit from sustained demand for large-scale computing capacity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Reflection also gains a critical advantage through guaranteed access to Nvidia GB300 chips, allowing the startup to focus on product development rather than infrastructure buildout. The company must deliver competitive AI models to rival OpenAI, Anthropic, and Google offerings.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/spacex-secures-6-3b-compute-deal-with-reflection-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal">SpaceX Secures $6.3B Compute Deal With Reflection AI</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
