					<description><![CDATA[<p>Upscale AI Raises Fresh Capital To Scale AI Networking Platform Upscale AI announced a $190 million Series A-1 funding round amid accelerating AI infrastructure demand. Premji Invest led the round</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/upscale-ai-raises-190m-to-expand-ai-networking-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal">Upscale AI Raises $190M to Expand AI Networking Infrastructure</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Upscale AI Raises Fresh Capital To Scale AI Networking Platform</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Upscale AI announced a $190 million Series A-1 funding round amid accelerating AI infrastructure demand. Premji Invest led the round with investment from NVIDIA, Salesforce Ventures, Seligman Ventures, Temasek, Mayfield, Tiger Global, StepStone Group, Maverick Silicon, and Prosperity7 Ventures. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Upscale AI&#8217;s funding to date stands at $500 million and marks a $2 billion company valuation. Based in Santa Clara, Upscale AI will leverage funds to fuel operations and scale deployments of its AI-native networking solutions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chief Executive Officer Barun Kar said networking remains one of the largest bottlenecks in modern AI infrastructure. He noted the company’s platform is designed to support growing demand for open and interoperable AI systems across hyperscale environments.</span></p>
<h2><b>Open-Standard Architecture Targets AI Infrastructure Bottlenecks</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The rapid expansion of artificial intelligence is placing increasing pressure on data centre networks. Several existing systems predated big-scale AI modeling systems and could not serve highly synchronous workloads such as for training or inference. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In response, Upscale AI is constructing an end-to-end AI networking platform, silicon, systems, software to provide a unique AI fabric and communication path between memory, storage, and accelerators in large-scale clusters to resolve any communication bottlenecks.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It also does so with open standards and without proprietary software. Management believes heterogeneous computing environments will become increasingly important as enterprises scale AI infrastructure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Lead investor Premji Invest said Upscale AI is addressing a critical challenge in the AI ecosystem. The firm cited the company’s technical progress and differentiated approach as key reasons for supporting the round.</span></p>
<h2><b>Growing Demand From Hyperscalers And Cloud Providers</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203015" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203015" class="size-full wp-image-203015" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Upscale-2.png" alt="Illustration of hyperscale AI data centers connected through advanced networking infrastructure, showing stable high-performance data flows across global cloud and neocloud providers." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203015" class="wp-caption-text">Growing demand from hyperscalers and cloud providers is accelerating investment in AI networking infrastructure, with scalable architectures and open standards enabling reliable performance across large distributed AI compute clusters. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Upscale AI is already working with several hyperscale operators and neocloud infrastructure providers. Customer evaluations and deployments are underway across both scale-out and scale-up networking environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These partnerships help position Salesforce to capitalize on increasing investment in artificial intelligence infrastructure. In fact, the global market for AI networking gear may climb past $100 billion a year by 2030 as the world’s tech companies construct much bigger AI clusters. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“The world is moving towards large-scale infrastructure that does not rely on any single cloud vendor,” Salesforce Ventures said in a statement. The firm believes open networking standards will become an important component of future AI deployments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors also highlighted Upscale AI’s zero-packet-loss architecture, which helps maintain consistent performance during intensive AI workloads. Reliable networking performance is increasingly important as training costs and model complexity continue to grow.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/bionyra-pharma-raises-165m-for-immune-disease-treatments/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Bionyra Pharma Raises $165M to Advance Next-Generation Immune Disease Treatments</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Experienced Founders Pursue Long-Term Growth Opportunity</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investor confidence in Upscale AI is reinforced by the experience of its leadership team. Executive Chairman Rajiv Khemani previously founded Innovium, which was acquired by Marvell in a transaction valued at approximately $1.1 billion. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">He also held senior leadership positions at Intel and Cavium. Barun Kar brings extensive networking expertise from previous roles at Palo Alto Networks and Juniper Networks. Upscale AI was initially incubated within Auradine, a company focused on blockchain and AI technologies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Despite strong momentum, competition in AI networking remains intense. Major technology companies continue investing heavily in </span><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/proprietary" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">proprietary</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> networking systems, while startups are raising significant capital to pursue similar opportunities.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, investors believe the long-term opportunity remains substantial. As generative AI drives demand for larger computing environments, networking is becoming a critical component of overall AI performance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With $500 million in total funding and a growing customer pipeline, Upscale AI is positioning itself as a significant player in next-generation AI infrastructure. The company believes open-standard networking will drive future AI innovation across cloud environments.</span></p>
