					<description><![CDATA[<p>Bionyra Pharma Launches With $165M Series A Financing Bionyra Pharma, a clinical-stage biotech, is taking flight out of stealth after raising $165 million Series A funding to advance a portfolio</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/bionyra-pharma-raises-165m-for-immune-disease-treatments/" data-wpel-link="internal">Bionyra Pharma Raises $165M to Advance Next-Generation Immune Disease Treatments</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Bionyra Pharma Launches With $165M Series A Financing</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Bionyra Pharma, a clinical-stage biotech, is taking flight out of stealth after raising $165 million Series A funding to advance a portfolio of biologic drugs designed to treat immune-mediated inflammatory diseases. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This funding was co-led by Jeito Capital and Sofinnova Partners, with contributions from Apollo Health Ventures, Arkin Bio, Sixty Degree Capital, Sanofi Ventures and Vives Partners. Based in Paris and Boston, Bionyra develops advanced antibody therapies for patients suffering from severe inflammatory diseases. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">These funds are expected to aid the company in bolstering R&amp;D and clinical programs, and growing out the team and operations. The company is starting its launch with a set of clinical and near-clinical drug candidates for patients struggling in areas where established options fall short. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CEO Frédéric Marrache said many inflammatory disease patients still experience inadequate disease control despite existing treatment options. Bionyra aims to leverage its pipeline to target immune pathways known to be key for the inflammatory process and offer treatments for more sustained response.</span></p>
<h2><b>Pipeline Targets Major Gaps in Inflammatory Disease Care</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Bionyra enters the market with a portfolio of biologics designed to address unmet needs in inflammatory bowel disease and atopic dermatitis. Its strategy combines multi-target biology with half-life extension technology to improve treatment durability.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s lead candidate, BYN-002, is a TL1A monoclonal antibody for inflammatory bowel disease and related conditions. The therapy is currently undergoing a fully enrolled Phase 1 study in healthy volunteers. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Management believes its extended half-life profile could support best-in-class potential. A second programme, BYN-003, is a bispecific antibody targeting both TL1A and IL-23p19. The therapy entered clinical testing earlier this year and is currently being evaluated in a Phase 1 trial. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Bionyra believes the dual-target approach could deliver stronger disease control than single-target therapies. The company is also advancing BYN-001, an IL-25 monoclonal antibody designed for atopic dermatitis and other Type 2 inflammatory diseases. </span></p>
<h2><b>Licensing Strategy Accelerates Clinical Development</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203011" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203011" class="size-full wp-image-203011" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Bionyra-2.png" alt="Illustration of licensed biotech assets entering a unified clinical development pipeline, showing accelerated drug discovery and global pharmaceutical collaboration." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203011" class="wp-caption-text">Strategic licensing is accelerating biotechnology innovation by enabling faster clinical development, leveraging pre-validated research assets, and streamlining the path from discovery to human trials. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Rather than building programmes entirely through internal discovery, Bionyra assembled its pipeline through strategic licensing agreements. Bionyra licensed BYN-002 and BYN-003 from TrueLab, plus BYN-001 from NovaRock with global rights.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This approach enables faster clinical development by leveraging assets that have already progressed through key research stages. Several programmes have already entered human testing, reducing the timeline typically required for early-stage biotechnology companies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Marrache said biotechnology firms often move faster than larger pharmaceutical organisations due to their focused development approach. He added that Bionyra selected targets with strong scientific rationale and opportunities to improve current treatment standards.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s leadership team combines pharmaceutical development expertise with scientific and clinical experience in immune-mediated diseases, providing a foundation for executing its development strategy.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/france-raises-e13-billion-to-boost-european-tech-investment/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">France Raises €13 Billion to Boost European Tech Investment</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Investors Back Growing Demand for Advanced Biologics</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investor interest in immune and inflammatory disease therapies remains strong across the biotechnology sector. Bionyra&#8217;s pipeline could develop improved biologic medications since patients cannot achieve long-lasting </span><a href="https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/articles/24673-cancer-remission" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">remission</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> on most treatments. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mehdi Ainouche Jeito Capital Partner. Bionyra looks poised to move the most promising of therapies toward successful clinical progress, he wrote in an e-mail. &#8220;In Bionyra, the team has the right talent to help address significant unmet needs in populations that do not respond well to existing treatments&#8221;.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sofinnova Partners, an initial seed funder, helped start Bionyra and was also enthusiastic about the start-up&#8217;s leadership.Partner Anta Gkelou said the oversubscribed financing reflects strong investor confidence in Bionyra’s management team and strategy. </span>Bionyra advances clinical studies and assets toward becoming immunology therapeutics leader.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
